f(x) = (\mathbf x ^ \top \mathbf x) ^ {p/2}
\nabla f(x) = 2p (\mathbf x ^ \top \mathbf x) ^ {(p-2)/2} \mathbf x
\nabla^2f(x) 
    \frac{\partial^2}{\partial x_i \partial x_j} \left( x_k x_k \right)^{p/2} = \frac{\partial}{\partial x_i} \left\{ p \left( x_k x_k \right)^{p/2-1} x_j \right\} = p \left( x_k x_k \right)^{p/2-1} \delta_{i,j} - p(p-2) \left( x_k x_k \right)^{p/2-2} x_i x_j 
   \nabla \otimes \nabla f(x) = p \left( x^\top x \right)^{p/2-1} \mathbb{I} - p(p-2) \left( x^\top x \right)^{p/2-2} x \otimes x^\top 
